entries.femaleVariant: Don't venture off too far, OK? Our sets'll lose sync.
Ah! Closed... Shame.
Aaarrghhh!
Could look for another way inside.
Be my guest.
Why didn't they take 'em?
Fell off your diner, it seems.
And this?
Doesn't get any more out of place than this.
Found a photo camera.
A framed photo, here?
Hockey stick?
Played this moment, coming back, so many times in my head.
Taken me years... workin' up the nerve for this.
Why didn't you come earlier?
Good question... Easy answer would be that I didn't have time, gear, stars weren't ever aligned…
Heh. Church hasn't aged at all. Always looked old and... like it'd landed here from outer space.
Bells were cracked too. Gave off this eerie, atonal clang.
You like going to this church?
entries.maleVariant: Did you like goin' to this church?

entries.femaleVariant: Think I hear them, too.
Don't know how it's possible, but... think I hear those bells too.
entries.maleVariant: I don't know how it's possible, but... I think I hear those bells too.

entries.femaleVariant: Seriously? You can hear my memories...? Must be a side effect.
Never actually "went" to church. Never even really paid attention to it, it was just... there, y'know?
We lookin' for anything in particular here?
Nah. Can't hurt to look around, though. Pickin' up very chill vibes.
After that we can see what lies up ahead.
Let's keep going.
I gotta say, don't really get why they left their wheels behind when they had to evacuate.
entries.maleVariant: Gotta say, I don't really get why they left their wheels behind when they had to evacuate.

entries.femaleVariant: This isn't yours?
And this? What is it?
It's hard to imagine anything that could be more out of place in an underwater world.
entries.maleVariant: Hard to imagine anything that could be more out of place in an underwater world.

entries.femaleVariant: Hey, how old you think I am?! These hunks of metal have got half a century on 'em.
When I was about yea high they were already here... and not in much better shape.
Alvarez! Where's Fifi?! Give her baaack!
Poor thing... Been here all alone for twenty years...
I don't have your stupid doll! But we can look for it together.
You took her doll?
As if!
Hid it... Was a monster…
Oh, no way! Can't be! You found the Heart of Laguna Bend!
Never noticed how... built-for-purpose this square was.
Ugh... I remember these beaters.
Wanna mosey around the square?
Holler if you wanna keep on movin'.
Let's keep goin', Judy.
Whaddaya say we move on?
Got no idea how weird it feels, swimming through here…
Was this... a bar?
Flo's Diner – best eatery in town. Only one at that too... Burgers weren't amazing. Too greasy, big.
What about your parents?
Dad was never in the picture. Mom died when I was tiny. Can barely remember her.
Still have her picture, but y'know... see a stranger there.
Judy, Judy, watch out for her cooties!
Alvarez is so poor, she can't even afford to have parents! Hahaha!
I want to keep going.
Wanna take a look around?
What was it like – livin' with your grandparents? How were they?
Here's where our gang used to play.
Square seemed huge to me back then.
Don't wanna stick around, sightsee?
Bored already? We can move on if you want.
Wanna see what's further on.
Looks like this fell off your "one and only" eatery.
Let's see now, your childhood tasted like scopdogs from Capitán Caliente. With habanero sauce, extra hot.
Gotta feel the burn.
You know what they say – it ain't Caliente if it don't burn on the way in... and out.
I don't even know what's real anymore.
Now let's see... Childhood for you tasted like sushi with real rice.
Even got real fish sometimes.
Bigger family gatherings were great – that's where we got even real fish.
Now, let's see... Childhood for you tasted like... toasted marshmallows.
Cuz others would've gladly taken 'em.
Ah, that's nomad life for ya – can't be a fussy eater or you'll get no food at all.
entries.maleVariant: That's nomad life for ya – can't be a fussy eater or you'll get no food at all.

entries.femaleVariant: I don't even know anymore. It's hard to separate actual memories from what you want to remember.
This tech's seriously next-level. You hear my thoughts?
entries.maleVariant: This tech is seriously next-level. You hear my thoughts?

entries.femaleVariant: This tech can read minds? Wow.
[Give camera] This is for you.
Weird place for a framed picture.
entries.maleVariant: That's a weird place for a framed picture.

entries.femaleVariant: Hockey stick? Was there a skating rink here?
Quit schmoozin', Alvarez! We're losin' 'cause of you!
Come on. Let's you and me swim a bit further.
Pfft, do I!
Just lemme know when you wanna forge ahead.
Come on, then. Wanna show you somethin'.
Ah, if it wa'n't so damned big, I'd take it home, hang it in my kitchen.
'Course, tasted even better when you stole 'em off the stand.
Used to stuff a few in your mouth at once and pretend you were a giant.
They always caught fire, burned, but that never bothered you.
Get echoes... and sense intentions too.
Not all the time, though.
Water probably carried it outta someone's house.
I wish. Played street hockey on rollerblades.
Coming! They're dead meat anyway!
So... will you go out with me?
Aye, aye, cap'n. Follow me.
Truth is, the very idea just felt... weird.
'Sides, didn't wanna come here alone... or with some rando.
Once we knew Laguna Bend was to be flooded, people gathered here to plan a protest.
Did it achieve anything?
Look around...
Weird... I had no memory of that seconds ago. Now I can almost hear 'em.
Feels like we're outside of time – like, in a snow globe.
S'good cover for playing MaxTac and psychos, though.
So it is yours?
Nah... It was Jenni Chapman's.
You hid it? W-why?
'Cause I thought only losers played with dolls... What I really wanted was for her to notice me.
The most precious gem in all Cali, maybe even the world. Could buy all of Arasaka and Militech and then some for it!
For real?
Pffttt... Hahaha! Nah, got no idea what that is.
Mmm... Bottled water?
Haha, touché, Judy, touché.
Where you used to run as a kid. Where daily life grinded along. Can imagine it a bit.
Props to the urban planners.
'Course, I say that now. Back then they were the best thing I'd ever chewed and swallowed.
And next door... That's where we lived.
Me and my grandparents.
And grandma was... temperamental. Hot one second, cool as steel the next.
Grandad had a real knack for things technical. Taught me everything I know. And the stories he told… Ah, never got bored listening to 'em.
Where are your grandparents now?
Now I know where your temper comes from.
Where'd your grandparents go? Night City?
Temperamental, huh? Ah, that explains a lot. Dominant family trait?
entries.maleVariant: Temperamental, huh? Explains a lot. Is that a dominant family trait?

entries.femaleVariant: Heh, no idea what you're talkin' about.
Yeah, for a couple years. Rented the unit that's mine now.
But they hated the city. Moved up to Oregon. Still go and visit 'em sometimes.
Got somethin' here... Looks like an old photo cam.
DPI-350 – practically an antique.
Like it?
You kidding? It's awesome!
Here, take this camera. Better off in your hands than sittin' here, collectin' algae.
Gosh, thanks!
Ahh, the days when dolls were just kids' toys and nothing else...
Anything to make out?
No, not much.
Sorry, gotta go. They're callin'!
Feeder grub'd finally hit the spot – taste like my golden childhood days.
Well, our brains weren't built with perfect memory.
Liked synthfish more, though. Real fish was just too stinky.
entries.maleVariant: I liked synthfish more, though. Real fish was just too... stinky.

entries.femaleVariant: Anyway, all kinds of food tastes better with just a little burn.
entries.maleVariant: Anyway... all kinds of food tastes better with just a little burn.

entries.femaleVariant: Found an opening. Think we're safe to go through here.
entries.maleVariant: I found an opening. I think we're safe to go through here.

entries.femaleVariant: Snuck in here once when no one was around.
Didn't get chased out?
Can't hear you too well.
Didn't get... chased off?
Readin' you worse and worse…
entries.maleVariant: I'm readin' you worse and worse…

entries.femaleVariant: On my way.
Stood at the altar and tried to imagine what went through the padre's mind, lookin' at all those people.
Ran out myself. Echo I got back scared the living bejesus out of me.
Huh? I read you loud 'n' clear. Everything all right?
Then I screamed at the top of my lungs to check the acoustics.
Thought it was that crush I had on Jenni Chapman. All that guilt I tried yelling out... flew right back in my face.
Back then I wondered how he could read people's thoughts, know everything about 'em.
What were those voices?
What was that? Those voices...?
Voices? Didn't hear anything but you just now.
What about your parents?
Did you like living with your grandparents?
This isn't your doll?
You took her doll?
Don't come up too quick, or you'll hurt yourself.
You're comin' up too fast, V!
[Pick up]
Wanna look around?
[Pick up] For real?
Hey, found a way in. Through the roof.
